text: Hey <!channel>, my good friend Jarrett is in from Pgh and is camped out doing some work over near Echo. He's a miserable crank like me, so be sure to stop by and say hello!

text: <!channel> a friendly reminder that paper coffee cups and their lids are NOT recyclable :truck: unless our building's rules are different from residential ones?
Nope, you are correct, no difference for our building. I think that recycling guidelines printout confirms this. Thanks Jenny!
<@U0289USNA> - Did you sign up for Inbox for your personal account or your Uncorked?
I (mistakenly) chose Uncorked - so it doesn't look like it will let me in yet (only for personal accounts)
<@U02E3CRMA>: how did the design challenge go?

<@U026NB2U2>: I had to forward the invite email to an actual <http://gmail.com|gmail.com> address and use that.   Unfortunately while I can add Google apps accounts like uncorked, it won't display them.

<@U026PT0D7>: generally, successful. Gaston got a clean UI and use case put together, Kat got the phone kinda talking with the reader, Josh got the coin acceptor figured out, and Jarrett and I got NFC working on a couple cards
NFC card emulation in Android is nascent, but there's a real opportunity for us to put together a full phone+Arduino NFC stack that would be valuable for future projects
